sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / DSP API
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Controller as workflow-controller<br/>9090/TCP (metrics)<br/>6060/TCP (health)
    participant ArgoExec as argoexec<br/>(sidecar in workflow pod)
    participant UserContainer as User Container<br/>(workflow step)
    participant S3 as S3 / Minio<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant DB as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP (optional)

    Note over User,DB: Flow 1: Workflow Execution

    User->>K8sAPI: POST Workflow CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Watch event: Workflow created<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Pod for workflow step<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    Note over K8sAPI,ArgoExec: Pod created with argoexec<br/>as init + wait sidecar

    ArgoExec->>K8sAPI: Read workflow template<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    ArgoExec->>UserContainer: Execute user command<br/>(process-local, emissary pattern)
    UserContainer-->>ArgoExec: Execution complete + outputs
    ArgoExec->>S3: Upload artifacts<br/>Auth: AWS AccessKey/SecretKey
    S3-->>ArgoExec: Upload confirmed
    ArgoExec->>K8sAPI: Create WorkflowTaskResult CR<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Update Workflow status<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token

    Note over User,DB: Flow 2: CronWorkflow Scheduling

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch CronWorkflow CRs<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: CronWorkflow schedule triggered
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Workflow from CronWorkflow<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token

    Note over User,DB: Flow 3: Workflow Archival (Optional)

    Controller->>DB: Archive workflow data<br/>Auth: DB credentials from Secret<br/>Encryption: SSL/TLS (configurable)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Update Workflow annotations<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
